    <div class="contain">
        <div class="main-content">
            <div class="card">
                <h2>Historical Significance</h2>
                <p>
                    Rath Yatra, held annually in Puri, is one of the oldest chariot festivals in the world, dating back
                    over a thousand years. It celebrates Lord Jagannath’s journey with siblings Balabhadra and Subhadra
                    to the Gundicha Temple. Rooted in devotion and mythology, it reflects Odisha’s deep spiritual
                    heritage and attracts millions of pilgrims globally.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h2>Cultural Highlights</h2>
                <p>
                    The festival is a grand display of Odisha’s culture, with devotional chants, traditional music, and
                    vibrant processions. Artisans craft massive wooden chariots adorned with colorful canopies. Folk
                    dances and rituals like the sweeping of chariots by the Gajapati King highlight the region’s unique
                    traditions and communal harmony.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h2>Food and Cuisine</h2>
                <p>
                    During Rath Yatra, Puri comes alive with culinary offerings. Devotees savor temple prasad like
                    Khichdi and Dalma, alongside street treats such as Chhena Gaja and Rabdi. Vendors serve refreshing
                    drinks like Bela Pana and spicy snacks, creating a feast that complements the spiritual fervor.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h2>Shopping Experience</h2>
                <p>
                    The festival transforms Puri into a bustling market. Stalls sell religious souvenirs, Jagannath idols,
                    and Pattachitra artworks. Handwoven textiles, seashell crafts, and brass items draw crowds. Bargaining
                    adds excitement, offering visitors a chance to take home pieces of Odisha’s sacred artistry.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h2>Festive Atmosphere</h2>
                <p>
                    Rath Yatra fills Puri with an electric vibe. Massive chariots roll through streets amid chants of
                    “Jai Jagannath,” pulled by thousands of devotees. The air resonates with conch shells, bells, and
                    joyous cries. It’s a spectacle of faith and unity, blending devotion with celebration.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

